sql:
SELECT AVG(comment_count) AS average_comments_per_post
FROM posts
WHERE view_count > 30;

external_knowledge:
- "vibrant gardens" refers to categories where active posts have over 50 votes;
- "enthusiastic gardeners" are users who have made more than 10 posts and over 5 comments;
- "planted over a dozen flowers" means users have made more than 10 posts;
- "watered at least five of them" indicates users have made more than 5 comments;
- "blossoms" symbolizes votes on posts;
- "active in the year 2020" corresponds to posts submitted between January 1, 2020, and December 31, 2020.

sql:
SELECT AVG(post_views) AS AverageViewsPerUser
FROM user_analytics
WHERE post_views > 2;

SELECT title, content
FROM posts
WHERE comment_count > (SELECT AVG(comment_count) FROM posts);

SELECT user_id, post_views, post_comments, post_votes, last_activity
FROM user_analytics
ORDER BY last_activity DESC;
